                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-42-person436">
                  JOHN 
                  PAPE
               <interp inst="t18220417-42-person436" type="surname" value="PAPE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-42-person436" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-42-person436" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18220417-42-viclabel215" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220417-42-victim435 t18220417-42-viclabel215"></join>. I had a great coat to repair for Mr. Carr. The prisoner slept that night at my house out of charity, at my son's desire in the shop. I left the coat with him and my son, on the 4th of March, about eight o'clock. I returned in two hours, and he was gone with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-42-person437">
                  GEORGE 
                  PAPE
               <interp inst="t18220417-42-person437" type="surname" value="PAPE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-42-person437" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-42-person437" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with the prisoner. He put the coat on, walked up and down the room, and said what a swell he was; then went down, saying he would go to see if my brother knew him, but never returned. I met him on the 6th instant, at Chairing-Cross, and had him secured.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-42-person438">
                  JOHN 
                  LEWIS BATHGATE
               <interp inst="t18220417-42-person438" type="surname" value="LEWIS BATHGATE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-42-person438" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-42-person438" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am constable. I took him in charge. He said he was very sorry, and hoped the magistrate would forgive him; and he would enlist in the East India Service.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18220417-42-verdict216" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18220417-42-verdict216" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
